Source: nopoll
Version: 1.0.4
Upstream-URL: https://github.com/Comcast/nopoll.git
Upstream-Ref: 1.0.4
Build-Depends: autoconf, automake, libtool, libssl-dev

Package: libnopoll
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: WebSocket library - runtime
 noPoll is a OpenSource WebSocket implementation (RFC 6455), written in
 ANSI C, that allows building pure WebSocket solutions or to provide
 WebSocket support to existing TCP oriented applications. It provides
 both client and server API.
 .
 This package contains the runtime library.

Package: libnopoll-dev
Section: libdevel
Priority: optional
Depends: libnopoll (= ${version})
Description: WebSocket library - development files
 noPoll is a OpenSource WebSocket implementation (RFC 6455), written in
 ANSI C, that allows building pure WebSocket solutions or to provide
 WebSocket support to existing TCP oriented applications. It provides
 both client and server API.
 .
 This package contains headers and development files.
